On june 20, 2013
pickupsticks

This is a "limited conditions army building" competition.

Success will be measured by a ladder system similar to the Continuous Championship.
Anybody is welcome to play. Players may only have one army in the competition. A player may choose to retire an army if they have six troopers or more, and create a new army to replace them. Armies with five or fewer troopers may not be retired, but you may choose to mark them as inactive so that other players can skip you if you do not want to play any more.
The game goes on forever, new players may join at any time.
Adding an illegal trooper will result in permanent disqualification, so it is strongly advised to password protect your army.

What makes this different is that you have a limited selection of skills that may be chosen as starting skills for new troopers.
These skills are chosen at random by using the forum's random number generators: 2

If you want to take part then you must first make a post in this thread and roll the random dice five times.
The numbers you get will determine which skills you can choose from, referring to the list below. EVERY trooper in your army must start with one of the skills from you possible options. You may use each option as many times as you like. For example if your options are Frenetic, Twinoid, Smart, Sprinter, Dodger you may create an army where all twelve troopers start with Dodger. You could not add any trooper whose starting skill is not on your list, so for this case a trooper with grenade would not be permitted - but you could select grenade later as an option if offered.

Here is the list of possible starting skills and their corresponding numbers:

If you get 86-100 then you are allowed to roll TWO dice and choose between them (with any 86+ results in these two being re-rollable until you get a valid choice)
(This list is all of the level one possible skills as listed on the wiki.)

To choose your skills make a post in this thread that says "I want to take part" and roll the 100-sided dice five times in that post.
These will be your skills. Try to choose an army name that will suit them!
Add yourself to the bottom of the ranking with a line like this:

1. http://tinyurl.com/knife-fighters Knife Fighters / pickupsticks / 3-5-27-8-16

Which is to say:

Rank. URL and Army name / player name / numbers you rolled for your skills

If any rule clarifications are needed then post in this thread (and send me a message in case I don't check the thread for a while) and I'll make a ruling of some kind. Hopefully fair and wise rather than arbitrary and corrupt, but you never know.

Ready to fight? Let's go.

pickupsticks

Didn't deal with duplicate rolls in the initial post, so here's an arbitrary ruling.

Heads: if you roll the same number more than once you can re-roll it

Tails: if you roll the same number more than once you're just very unlucky, sorry!

Tails

pickupsticks
45424A little question - can we re-roll the skills when we reach 6 troopers and decide to start over?

Yes. The idea of the six-trooper thing is to stop people from re-rolling over and over until they get something they like the look of - you have to give your army a fair crack of the whip. If you get up to six troopers and don't think that they are going to be fun or successful enough to keep you happy then you can bin them and try your luck again by rerolling and starting from scratch.

Xtremekiwi
karryHow is it with 6-troopers? Wolf has 6 troopers and I think 5 is the max.

To quote the first post...

A player may choose to retire an army if they have six troopers or more, and create a new army to replace them. Armies with five or fewer troopers may not be retired, but you may choose to mark them as inactive so that other players can skip you if you do not want to play any more.

So you can have more than 5 troopers, it's just that with 6+ troopers you can retire your current army and roll a new set of numbers.
